applicable to your own interactions with the same bots or apps. </strong></p><h3 class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-1svpdpu"><strong class="framer-text">You have questions, we have answers  FAQs</strong></h3><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">What personal data does Poe collect? </strong>We collect information such as your name, email address, and IP address to create your Poe account. Please visit the <!--$--><a class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-15ebhor" href="https://poe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Poe Privacy Policy</a><!--/$--> to learn more.</p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">Can other Poe users see my chats? </strong>No, other users cant read your chats with bots or apps on Poe unless you explicitly decide to share them (for example, by inviting another user into the chat) or interact with other users in a group chat.</p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">What does anonymized chats mean? </strong>The personal data associated with your Poe account (e.g. name and email) is not sent to our AI model providers  in other words, they do not know who you are when they receive the contents of your chats from us.</p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">Are my chats shared with third parties? </strong>We share the contents of your chats with AI model providers that power the bots and apps on Poe (including OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, and Meta), and with third-party developers if you interact with half shield bots or apps. Although we take steps to help keep your identity private, any personal data you include in your chats with the bots or apps is shared with the AI model providers and may be shared with developers (remember, please use caution and avoid sharing sensitive information, such as your credit card number, with the bots and apps).</p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">Are my chats used to train the AI models? </strong>In most cases, no. Only third-party developer bots and apps are permitted to use your chats to train their models. You can check the bots or apps privacy shield icon to find out what type of bot or app it is.</p><ul class="framer-text"><li data-preset-tag="p" class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3">Official Poe bots and user-created prompt bots using Open AI, Anthropic, Google, and Metas AI models do <strong class="framer-text">not </strong>train on your chats and cannot access your chats for anything other than to produce the requested LLM response</p></li><li data-preset-tag="p" class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3">Third-party developer bots and apps can use your chats to train their AI models  even then, they dont have access to the personal data associated with your Poe account unless you interact with other users in a group chat.</p></li></ul><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">What happens when I delete my chats? How about when I delete my Poe account? </strong>Your chats and personal data associated with your account are deleted from Poes systems and will not be used for any other purpose. Visit the <!--$--><a class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-15ebhor" href="https://help.poe.com/hc/en-us/articles/19944206309524-Poe-FAQs#h_01HCFXCW5CMZ0MWHG2EJ6TJN38" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Poe Help Center</a><!--/$--> to learn how to find these settings.</p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">How long do your AI model provider partners retain my chats for? </strong>Each provider sets their own retention schedule (e.g. OpenAI and Anthropic retain your chats for 30 days). Please reach out to the AI model provider directly to learn more.</p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><br class="framer-text trailing-break"></p></div></div></div><div style="transform:none"><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">Your trust is important to us. </strong>We are committed to building and maintaining your trust  and that starts with being transparent about what we do to protect your privacy when you use Poe.</p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">At a quick glance</strong></p><ul class="framer-text"><li data-preset-tag="p" class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3">Your interactions with bots and apps are only visible to you and the model provider, unless you (1) share them, (2) interact with other users in group chats, or (3) interact with half shield bots or apps (see below), in which case the developers who created those bots or apps may be able to see them.</p></li><li data-preset-tag="p" class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3">Your interactions with bots and apps are aggregated or anonymized before they are shared with AI model providers or developers, unless you interact with other users in group chats, in which case AI model providers and developers may receive limited personally identifiable information to help the model distinguish between users.</p></li></ul><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">Understanding the privacy shield </strong></p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3">Every bot or app has a privacy shield icon that indicates how it will handle your chats. You can find the privacy shield icon in the bot or app info card: </p><img alt width="960" height="540" src="https://framerusercontent.com/images/ScFgIRWYdge42vTDMfQ1F2vtsM.png" class="framer-text">Privacy Shield Permissions</strong></p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3">A bot or app can change from full shield to half shield if you grant it new permissions. If you grant new permissions for a specific interaction, the privacy shield that applies to that interaction will be visible in the message info page: </p><img alt width="960" height="540" class="framer-text">When interacting with other users, please see the message info page for the shield level that applied to any message or query in that chat, which may differ from the shield level applicable to your own interactions with the same bots or apps. </strong></p><h3 class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-1svpdpu"><strong class="framer-text">You have questions, we have answers  FAQs</strong></h3><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">What personal data does Poe collect? </strong>We collect information such as your name, email address, and IP address to create your Poe account. Please visit the <!--$--><a class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-15ebhor" href="https://poe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Poe Privacy Policy</a><!--/$--> to learn more.</p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">Can other Poe users see my chats? </strong>No, other users cant read your chats with bots or apps on Poe unless you explicitly decide to share them (for example, by inviting another user into the chat) or interact with other users in a group chat.</p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">What does anonymized chats mean? </strong>The personal data associated with your Poe account (e.g. name and email) is not sent to our AI model providers  in other words, they do not know who you are when they receive the contents of your chats from us.</p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">Are my chats shared with third parties? </strong>We share the contents of your chats with AI model providers that power the bots and apps on Poe (including OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, and Meta), and with third-party developers if you interact with half shield bots or apps. Although we take steps to help keep your identity private, any personal data you include in your chats with the bots or apps is shared with the AI model providers and may be shared with developers (remember, please use caution and avoid sharing sensitive information, such as your credit card number, with the bots and apps).</p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">Are my chats used to train the AI models? </strong>In most cases, no. Only third-party developer bots and apps are permitted to use your chats to train their models. You can check the bots or apps privacy shield icon to find out what type of bot or app it is.</p><ul class="framer-text"><li data-preset-tag="p" class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3">Official Poe bots and user-created prompt bots using Open AI, Anthropic, Google, and Metas AI models do <strong class="framer-text">not </strong>train on your chats and cannot access your chats for anything other than to produce the requested LLM response</p></li><li data-preset-tag="p" class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3">Third-party developer bots and apps can use your chats to train their AI models  even then, they dont have access to the personal data associated with your Poe account unless you interact with other users in a group chat.</p></li></ul><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">What happens when I delete my chats? How about when I delete my Poe account? </strong>Your chats and personal data associated with your account are deleted from Poes systems and will not be used for any other purpose. Visit the <!--$--><a class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-15ebhor" href="https://help.poe.com/hc/en-us/articles/19944206309524-Poe-FAQs#h_01HCFXCW5CMZ0MWHG2EJ6TJN38" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Poe Help Center</a><!--/$--> to learn how to find these settings.</p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><strong class="framer-text">How long do your AI model provider partners retain my chats for? </strong>Each provider sets their own retention schedule (e.g. OpenAI and Anthropic retain your chats for 30 days). Please reach out to the AI model provider directly to learn more.</p><p class="framer-text framer-styles-preset-198gsp3"><br class="framer-text trailing-break"></p></div></div></div><div conversationStarters: Create a fictitious language, explain how it works, and write a short story in it.
A pond has lily pads that double in number every day. On day 8, there are 32 lily pads. On which day will there be 256 lily pads?
defaultBotObject.description:
Claude Opus 4.5 from Anthropic, supports customizable thinking budget (up to 64k tokens) and 200k context window.
To instruct the bot to use more thinking effort, add --thinking_budget and a number ranging from 0 to 63999 to the end of your message.
